cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving the robustness of machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically addresses the issue of supervisory signals in the training process, which is related to the sub-field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed Max-Mahalanobis center loss is a novel technique for improving robustness, which could also be relevant to the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
